      "content": "Fortigate Firewall Course Outline\n========================\n1. Introduction to Fortinet and FortiOS\n    - Fortinet Overview\n    - Understanding FortiOS and Key Features\n    - Fortinet Security Fabric Architecture\n2. Basic Firewall Concepts\n    - Understanding Firewall Policies\n    - Security Profiles Configuration\n    - Logging and Monitoring Basics\n3. Network Address Translation (NAT)\n    - Source NAT Configuration with single LAN Network \n    - Source NAT Configuration with  Multiple  LAN Network\n    - Source NAT Configuration with Cisco layer2 Switch for Multiple Vlan Network\n    - Destination NAT Configuration (Public Servers Over Internet) \n    - NAT Rules and Troubleshooting\n4 . Web Proxy and loadbalancing\n    - Web proxy server theory\n    - Configure fortigate web proxy \n    - Configure server loadbalancing\n    - Configure Interface aggregation \n5 . User Authentication\n     - User Groups and Authentication Methods\n     - Captive Portal Configuration\n     - Integration with External Authentication Servers\n6. Virtual Private Networks (VPN)\n     - Introduction to IPsec and SSL VPNs\n     - VPN Configuration\n     - VPN Troubleshooting\n7. FortiGate Routing\n     - Static Routing\n     - Policy-Based Routing\n     - Dynamic Routing Protocols Overview\n8. High Availability (HA)\n     - HA Concepts and Modes\n     - HA Configuration and Synchronization\n     - Failover and Troubleshooting\n9. Advanced Threat Protection\n     - FortiGuard Services Overview\n     - Web Filtering, Application Control, \nand Antivirus\n     - Intrusion Prevention System (IPS)\n10. FortiGate Management and Maintenance\n     - FortiManager Basics\n     - Firmware Management\n     - Backup and Restore Configurations\n11. Troubleshooting Techniques\n      - Common FortiGate Issues\n      - Diagnostic Tools and Commands\n      - Logs and Reports",
